      "label": "E2E Shared SQLite Database Isolation Issue",
      "file_type": "document",
      "source_file": "apps/dms-material-e2e/README.md",
      "source_location": "## Database Isolation Issue",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "problem": "Chromium and Firefox share single test-database.db; parallel execution causes SQLite locking and data pollution",
      "cause": "Default Playwright parallel execution interleaves tests between browsers against same DB"
    },
    {
      "id": "e2e_sequential_execution",
      "label": "E2E Sequential Browser Execution Strategy",
      "file_type": "document",
      "source_file": "apps/dms-material-e2e/README.md",
      "source_location": "### Solution",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "solution": "Run browsers sequentially (complete one browser before starting the next) via separate pnpm scripts",
      "scripts": [
        "pnpm e2e:dms-material:chromium",
        "pnpm e2e:dms-material:firefox"
      ],
      "future_improvements": [
        "Separate databases per browser (chromium-test.db, firefox-test.db)",
        "beforeEach/afterEach hooks to reset DB state",
        "Transaction rollback per test",
        "Separate backend instances on different ports"
      ]
